content:
Capture a Snapshot of a Scratch Org's Configuration with Scratch Org Snapshots (Generally Available)

This feature captures a snapshot of a scratch org's configuration, allowing you to use it to create scratch org replicas. The snapshot is a point-in-time copy of the scratch org.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Developer, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions.

When: This feature will be available on a rolling basis starting in late June 2024.

Why: Configuring a scratch org with a project's dependencies can be manual and time-consuming. Scratch org snapshots allow you to quickly replicate scratch orgs with required project dependencies.

How: Enable Scratch Org Snapshots in the Dev Hub org using Setup, then use Salesforce CLI commands to create and manage the snapshot.
title: Capture a Scratch Org's Configuration with Snapshots
